Everett Crosby, owns a vineyard only 28 miles from New York on the Hudson, and each Labor Day weekend we bring our family to picnic lunch, and help him gather the harvest. It may be coincidence or envy, but anyhow, Mr. Crosby believes his 1959 is a great vintage year, the best white wine he has ever made, and the cream of his harvest bears the label ‘Special Reserve” and he charges a little more for it. Here is a wine we think you will like, it is native to New York and it is our own ‘vin du pays’.
